In article <36078l$kh5@cville-srv.wam.umd.edu> rsrodger@wam.umd.edu (R S Rodgers) writes:

> Using the term "selling" loosely, of course.  The sales from September
> onward seem more a measure of just how fast IBM can give OS/2 away than how
> fast they could actually _sell_ it.

I'd say that's true.  $15 for an operating system is effectively free.
IBM says that what they're doing is inventory-clearing; I'm inclined
to believe them.

Of course, giving away copies of an operating system has sometimes
been a pretty effective marketing tactic; if nothing else, it leads to
greater visibility.  From what I've heard, some of the success of
Windows 3.0 was because Microsoft gave away a lot of copies of Windows
2.0.
--

